gov.sandia.rbb.impl.h2.statics
Class H2STimeseries

java.lang.Object
  gov.sandia.rbb.impl.h2.statics.H2STimeseries

public class H2STimeseries
extends java.lang.Object

H2STimeseries contains static methods that are stored procedures in the H2 implementation of RBB Time Series The create_rbb.sql script creates aliases for these so they can be called through SQL. The public functions here only accept / return datatypes for which H2 has a SQL mapping. Most functionality is placed here, with the RBB interface implementation (H2Timeseries) being a thin wrapper over them.

resampleValues

public static java.sql.ResultSet resampleValues(java.sql.Connection conn,
                                                java.lang.Object[] IDs_,
                                                java.lang.Double[] times,
                                                java.lang.String timeCoordinate)
                                         throws java.sql.SQLException
Return linearly interpolated values of the specified timeseries (specified by IDs) at the specified times.

Any values previous to the timeseries start or after the end are NULL.

Any values at or after the timeseries start but before the first sample are extrapolated from the first two samples, unless there's only one sample in which case that value is used. Likewise for values before or at the end but after the last sample.

NULL values generated for an ID that corresponds to an Event that is not a Timeseries.

If times==null, the sample times of the first timeseries (IDs_[0]) are used, limited to the times at which all the Events exist. In this case the first ID cannot be an event, it must be a timeseries.

If this operation fails because one of the timeseries identified by IDs_ is empty, then the SQL state of the raised exception will be RBB_EMPTY_TIMESERIES.

Throws:
java.sql.SQLException

getSamples

public static java.sql.ResultSet getSamples(java.sql.Connection conn,
                                            long id,
                                            java.lang.Double start,
                                            java.lang.Double end,
                                            int numBefore,
                                            int numAfter,
                                            java.lang.String timeCoordinate_,
                                            H2STime.Cache timeCache)
                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
Retrieve samples for the specified timeseries, including those at or after after 'start' plus the last 'numBefore' samples before 'start', and likewise for end/numAfter.

The returned columns are:
TIME, SAMPLE
where each row of DATA is an array. and can be parsed by Timeseries.SampleCopy(ResultSet rs)

dataDims is the number of dimensions of rows to retrieve. If 0, only the times are returned. This number may not be larger than the dimensionality of the timeseries.

If timeCoordinate is non-null, then start/end are specified in this time coordinate and the times of the returned samples are converted to it. If non-null, timeCache is used to get the time conversion parameters.

start and/or end may be null. In this case all the samples starting from the first (or up the last) are returned, and numBefore (or numAfter) is ignored.

Throws:
java.sql.SQLException

valueLinear

public static java.lang.Float[] valueLinear(java.sql.Connection conn,
                                            long id,
                                            java.lang.Double time,
                                            java.lang.String timeCoordinate)
                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
Retrieve the value of the specified timeseries using linear interpolation. If there is a sample before and after the time, those two samples will be used. Otherwise, the value will be extrapolated from the last two values before the specified time (or first two after the specified time, as the case may be). If there is only one sample, its value is assumed constant for all time. If there are no samples, an exception is thrown. If a timeCoordinate is passed, it is a tagset specifying a time coordinate for the 'time' parameter, e.g. 'timeCoordinate=sessionSeconds,session=2010_04_21__17_24_29' timeCoordinate may be null, in which case the 'time' parameter is interpreted to be in whatever time coordinate the timeseries is stored.

Throws:
java.sql.SQLException

findNearest

public static java.sql.ResultSet findNearest(java.sql.Connection conn,
                                             java.lang.String filterTags,
                                             java.lang.Object[] pt,
                                             double time,
                                             java.lang.String timeCoordinate,
                                             java.lang.Double maxDist,
                                             java.lang.Integer maxResults)
                                      throws java.sql.SQLException
Find the timeseries whose values are nearest the specified point at the specified time, sorted by distance (low to high) Example sql: call rbb_find_nearest_timeseries(('test','draw'), (972, 367), 6.416, null, 50, 99);

Parameters:
conn -
filterTags: - Only timeseries with at least these tags will be found. Not null.
pt: - the target point. Not null.
time: - the target time. not null.
maxDist: - If not null, only results within this distance will be found.
maxResults: - If not null, will return at most this many results.
Returns:
The returned ResultSet contains the same columns as from H2SEvent.find, plus: X: the value of the timeseries at the specified time. DIST: the distance from the query point example: ID START_TIME END_TIME TAGS DATA_SCHEMA DATA_TABLE X DIST 3 0.729 9.184 (color, red, test, draw, type, drawing) RBB_TIMESERIES S3 (936.25397, 377.96826) 37.39093 5 5.368 9.641 (color, green, test, draw, type, drawing) RBB_TIMESERIES S5 (986.17163, 406.17163) 41.656353
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException
